            <h1> How to program a website </h1>
            <h2> by us! </h2>
            <p>First you need to learn a few languages:  HTML, CSS and JavaScript
                (also known as <span id = 'w1'>ECMA</span> SCRIPT).  Take about a 
                <span id = 'w2'>month</span> on each language, practicing every 
                day for at least <span id = 'w3'>30</span> - 
                <span id = 'w4'>60</span> minutes.  Also, every day, read!  
                There are books, smartphone apps and cheatsheets that you can 
                <span id = 'w5'>read </span> every day.</p>

            <p>Make flashcards of <span id = 'w6'>new</span> concepts and 
                techniques. <span id = 'w7'>Writing</span> the flashcards helps 
                commit the knowledge to memory better than just 
                <span id = 'w8'>reading</span> it.  Also, when you see a sample 
                of code meant to only show you an example, write that out!  
                Then save a separate file containing just that code, within a 
                bare-bones HTML document.</p>

            <p>The first time that you start working for money is always going 
                to be intimidating.  The better you know your stuff, the more 
                confident you'll be when they test you and ask you questions 
                that really get you thinking.</p>

            <p> STUDY EVERY DAY!  At least 30 - 60 minutes of SOME form of 
                repetition. Repetition is the key for learning anything.  
                Repeat the information, even after you feel you know it.  
                Check out the methods of learning, out there on the internet.</p>
                <h1> THANKS FOR PLAYING! </h1>
                <button onclick = 'location.reload(true)'>Start Again!</button>
